{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.4.0"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":131588,"databundleVersionId":15785849}],"dockerImageVersionId":31330,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"r","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Integrated AI-Driven Emergency Department Triage Decision Support System.**\n\n\nIntegrating structured data, clinical text, and comorbidity risk to enhance triage accuracy and early deterioration detection\n\n\n\n This notebook presents a **multi-modal AI system** designed to assist emergency department (ED) triage by:\n\n - Predicting **triage acuity (1–5)**\n - Interpreting **chief complaint text (NLP)**\n - Estimating **deterioration risk (1–10)**\n\n The approach combines **machine learning, rule-based NLP, and clinically informed risk scoring** into a unified decision-support pipeline.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\n# LOAD PACKAGES\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(janitor)\nlibrary(caret)\nlibrary(lightgbm)\nlibrary(stringr)\nlibrary(Matrix)\nlibrary(scales)\nlibrary(stringr)\n\nset.seed(123)\noptions(scipen = 999)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-13T23:45:23.174558Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-13T23:45:23.176001Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-13T23:45:23.19857Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-13T23:45:23.196699Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\n# PREDICT TRIAGE ACUITY LEVEL\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\ntrain_raw <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/triagegeist/train.csv\") %>%\n  clean_names() %>%\n  slice_sample(prop = 0.1) %>%\n  select(-disposition, -ed_los_hours)\n\ntest_raw <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/triagegeist/test.csv\") %>%\n  clean_names()\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------~\n# Create a levels dictionary from TRAIN ONLY\n# ------------------------------------------------------------~\n\nfactor_cols <- train_raw %>%\n  select(where(is.character), where(is.logical)) %>%\n  colnames()\n\n\nfactor_levels <- lapply(train_raw[factor_cols], function(x) {\n  sort(unique(x))\n})\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# FACTORISE (TRAIN + TEST SEPARATELY — NO LEAKAGE) \n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Factorise the train and test sets in the same way.\ntrain_raw <- train_raw %>%\n  mutate(across(\n    all_of(factor_cols),\n    ~ factor(.x, levels = factor_levels[[cur_column()]])\n  ))\n\n\ntest_raw <- test_raw %>%\n  mutate(across(\n    all_of(factor_cols),\n    ~ factor(.x, levels = factor_levels[[cur_column()]])\n  ))\n\n\n\n# Verify levels\n\nunseen_summary <- lapply(factor_cols, function(col) {\n  sum(is.na(test_raw[[col]]))\n})\nnames(unseen_summary) <- factor_cols\nunseen_summary\n\n\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# TRAIN / VALIDATION SPLIT\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Build group on FULL data (for split only)\ngroup_id_full <- interaction(\n  train_raw$site_id,\n  train_raw$arrival_mode,\n  train_raw$pain_location,\n  train_raw$mental_status_triage,\n  drop = TRUE\n)\n\nset.seed(123)\nfolds_full <- caret::groupKFold(group_id_full, k = 5)\n\nval_indices <- folds_full[[1]]\n\ntrain_fit <- train_raw[-val_indices, ]\ntrain_val <- train_raw[val_indices, ]\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# BUILD FOLDS (ONLY ON TRAIN_FIT ✅)\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\ngroup_id <- interaction(\n  train_fit$site_id,\n  train_fit$arrival_mode,\n  train_fit$pain_location,\n  train_fit$mental_status_triage,\n  drop = TRUE\n)\n\nset.seed(123)\nfolds <- caret::groupKFold(group_id, k = 5)\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# BUILD FOLDS\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# group_id_train <- interaction(train_raw$site_id, train_raw$arrival_mode, train_raw$pain_location, train_raw$mental_status_triage, drop = TRUE)\n# set.seed(123)\n# folds_train <- caret::groupKFold(group_id_train, k =5)\n# \n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# Factorise the train_val set in the same way as train and test.\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\ntrain_val <- train_val %>%\n  mutate(across(\n    all_of(factor_cols),\n    ~ factor(.x, levels = factor_levels[[cur_column()]])\n  ))\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# FEATURE / LABEL SPLIT\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\nX_train <- train_fit %>% select(-triage_acuity)\ny_train <- train_fit$triage_acuity\ny_train <- y_train - 1\n\nX_val <- train_val %>% select(-triage_acuity)\ny_val <- train_val$triage_acuity\ny_val <- y_val - 1\n\nX_test <- test_raw \n\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# MATRIX CONVERSION (LIGHTGBM‑R SAFE)\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\ntrain_matrix <- as.matrix(\n  mutate(X_train, across(all_of(factor_cols), as.integer)))\n\n\nval_matrix <- as.matrix(\n  mutate(X_val, across(all_of(factor_cols), as.integer)))\n\n\ntest_matrix <- as.matrix(\n  mutate(X_test, across(all_of(factor_cols), as.integer)))\n\n\n# # ------------------------------------------------------------\n# # CHECK OVERLY CORRELATED FEATURES\n# # ------------------------------------------------------------\n# cor_matrix <- cor(train_matrix, use = \"pairwise.complete.obs\")\n# \n# high_corr <- findCorrelation(cor_matrix, cutoff = 0.9)\n# high_corr \n# \n# length(high_corr)\n# \n# \n# # ------------------------------------------------------------\n# # REMOVE THOSE OVERLY CORRELATED COLUMNS\n# # ------------------------------------------------------------\n# \n# train_matrix <- train_matrix[, -high_corr]\n# val_matrix   <- val_matrix[, -high_corr]\n# test_matrix  <- test_matrix[, -high_corr]\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# CATEGORICAL FEATURE INDICES (ROBUST, REQUIRED)\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\ncategorical_features <- which(\n  colnames(train_matrix) %in% c(\n    \"site_id\", \"arrival_mode\", \"arrival_day\", \"arrival_season\",\n    \"shift\",\"age_group\",\"sex\",\"language\",\"insurance_type\",\n    \"transport_origin\",\"pain_location\",\n    \"mental_status_triage\", \"chief_complaint_system\"\n  )\n)\n\n\nstopifnot(length(categorical_features) > 0)\n\n\n\ndtrain <- lgb.Dataset(\n  data = train_matrix,\n  label = y_train,\n  categorical_feature = categorical_features\n)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-13T23:51:44.106359Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-13T23:51:44.108255Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-13T23:51:45.165414Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-13T23:51:45.163507Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# BASELINE MODEL FOR FEATURE IMPORTANCE\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndtrain_baseline <- lgb.Dataset(\n  data = train_matrix,\n  label = y_train,\n  categorical_feature = categorical_features\n)\n\nbaseline_params <- list(\n  objective = \"multiclass\",\n  num_class = 5,\n  metric = \"multi_logloss\",   \n  boosting = \"gbdt\",\n  learning_rate = 0.05,\n  num_leaves = 31,\n  feature_fraction = 0.9,\n  bagging_fraction = 0.8,\n  bagging_freq = 5,\n  verbosity = -1\n)\n\nbaseline_model <- lgb.train(\n  params = baseline_params,\n  data = dtrain_baseline,\n  nrounds = 200\n)\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n# FEATURE IMPORTANCE (VALID)\n# ------------------------------------------------------------\n\nimportance <- lgb.importance(baseline_model, percentage = TRUE)\nprint(importance)\nlgb.plot.importance(importance, top_n = 20)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-13T23:50:01.155551Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-13T23:50:01.157178Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-13T23:50:15.549809Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-13T23:50:15.54787Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cv_params <- list(\n  objective = \"multiclass\",\n  num_class = 5,\n  metric = \"multi_logloss\",\n  boosting = \"gbdt\",\n  verbosity = -1,\n  feature_pre_filter = FALSE,\n  \n  # Tree structure\n  max_depth = -1,\n  num_leaves = 63,\n  min_data_in_leaf = 80,      # 🔼 increase = less overfit\n  \n  # Sampling\n  feature_fraction = 0.75,\n  bagging_fraction = 0.8,\n  bagging_freq = 1,\n  \n  # Learning\n  learning_rate = 0.03,\n  \n  # Regularisation (stronger)\n  lambda_l1 = 1.0,\n  lambda_l2 = 5.0,\n  min_gain_to_split = 0.05,\n  \n  # Categorical\n  max_cat_to_onehot = 16,\n  cat_smooth = 30,\n  cat_l2 = 30,\n  \n  # Histogram\n  max_bin = 255\n)\n\n\ncv_final <- lgb.cv(\n  params = cv_params,\n  data = dtrain,\n  folds = folds,\n  nrounds = 2000,\n  early_stopping_rounds = 100,\n  verbose = -1\n)\n\nbest_iter <- cv_final$best_iter\n\nfinal_model <- lgb.train(\n  params = cv_params,\n  data = dtrain,\n  nrounds = best_iter\n)\n\nfinal_model","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-13T23:52:47.040073Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-13T23:52:47.041752Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-13T23:52:57.426446Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-13T23:52:57.424179Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"preds <- predict(final_model, test_matrix)\n\npred_matrix <- matrix(preds, ncol = 5, byrow = TRUE)\n\npred_class <- max.col(pred_matrix) - 1   # back to 0–4\npred_class <- pred_class + 1             # if you need 1–5\n\n\nprediction_df <- tibble(\n  test_raw,\n  triage_acuity = pred_class)\n\n\nhead(prediction_df)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-13T23:53:00.968768Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-13T23:53:00.970442Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-13T23:53:05.15873Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-13T23:53:05.15694Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\n# NLP: CHIEF COMPLAINT:\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\n# LOAD DATA\nchief_complaints <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/triagegeist/chief_complaints.csv\")\n\n\n# DICTIONARY\nrisk_dict <- list(\n  CRITICAL = c(\n    \"necrotising\", \"necrotizing\", \"sepsis\", \"haemothorax\",\n    \"loss of vision\", \"stroke\", \"facial droop\",\n    \"organ dysfunction\", \"cardiac arrest\",\n    \"hyperglycaemia\", \"severe weakness\"\n  ),\n  HIGH = c(\n    \"fever\", \">39\", \"rigors\", \"diaphoresis\",\n    \"rapidly spreading\", \"infection\",\n    \"abdominal pain\", \"pancreatitis\",\n    \"neurological\", \"near-syncope\"\n  ),\n  MODERATE = c(\n    \"worsening\", \"persistent\", \"intermittent\",\n    \"pain\", \"vomiting\", \"nausea\"\n  )\n)\n\n\n# TEXT CLEANING\nclean_text <- function(text) {\n  text %>%\n    tolower() %>%\n    str_replace_all(\"[^a-z0-9\\\\s><]\", \"\") %>%\n    str_squish()\n}\n\n\n# MATCH COUNT (supports phrases)\ncount_matches <- function(text, patterns) {\n  patterns <- str_replace_all(patterns, \" \", \"\\\\\\\\s+\")\n  str_count(text, str_c(patterns, collapse = \"|\"))\n}\n\n\n# SCORING FUNCTION (with escalation logic)\nscore_text <- function(text) {\n  \n  text <- clean_text(text)\n  score <- 0\n  \n  # base scoring (counts, not just presence)\n  for (level in names(risk_dict)) {\n    n <- count_matches(text, risk_dict[[level]])\n    \n    if (level == \"CRITICAL\") score <- score + 3 * n\n    if (level == \"HIGH\")     score <- score + 2 * n\n    if (level == \"MODERATE\") score <- score + 1 * n\n  }\n  \n  # ESCALATION RULES (clinical combinations)\n  \n  if (str_detect(text, \"fever\") & str_detect(text, \"rigors\")) {\n    score <- score + 2\n  }\n  \n  if (str_detect(text, \"worsening|rapidly\") & str_detect(text, \"pain|infection\")) {\n    score <- score + 2\n  }\n  \n  if (str_detect(text, \"sudden\") & str_detect(text, \"neurological|vision|weakness\")) {\n    score <- score + 3\n  }\n  \n  if (str_detect(text, \"necrotising|necrotizing\") & str_detect(text, \"rapid\")) {\n    score <- score + 4\n  }\n  \n  score\n}\n\n\n# CLASSIFICATION (adjusted thresholds for richer scoring)\nclassify_risk <- function(score) {\n  case_when(\n    score >= 5 ~ \"CRITICAL\",\n    score >= 3 ~ \"HIGH\",\n    score >= 1 ~ \"MODERATE\",\n    TRUE ~ \"LOW\"\n  )\n}\n\n# OPTIONAL SYSTEM-LEVEL PRIOR BOOST\nsystem_boost <- function(system) {\n  case_when(\n    system %in% c(\"cardiovascular\", \"neurological\", \"infectious\") ~ 1,\n    TRUE ~ 0\n  )\n}\n\n\n# SUMMARY TEXT\nsummarise_case <- function(text, risk) {\n  paste0(\n    \"[\", risk, \"] \",\n    str_trunc(str_to_sentence(text), 80)\n  )\n}\n\n\n# APPLY PIPELINE\ndf_nlp <- chief_complaints %>%\n  mutate(\n    base_score = map_dbl(chief_complaint_raw, score_text),\n    risk_score = base_score + system_boost(chief_complaint_system),\n    risk_level = classify_risk(risk_score),\n    summary = map2_chr(chief_complaint_raw, risk_level, summarise_case)\n  )\n\nhead(df_nlp)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-14T00:18:04.647561Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-14T00:18:04.649256Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-14T00:19:53.496962Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-14T00:19:53.494723Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\n# DETERIORATION RISK MODEL\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------~\npatient_history <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/triagegeist/patient_history.csv\")\ntest_raw_det <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/triagegeist/test.csv\") %>%\n  clean_names()\n\n# weighted risk score (0–10 scale)\ncreate_risk_score <- function(df) {\n  \n  df %>%\n    mutate(\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # CARDIOVASCULAR (highest risk)\n      # ----------------------------\n      cardio_score =\n        3 * hx_heart_failure +\n        2.5 * hx_coronary_artery_disease +\n        2 * hx_atrial_fibrillation +\n        2 * hx_stroke_prior +\n        1.5 * hx_peripheral_vascular_disease +\n        1 * hx_hypertension,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # RESPIRATORY\n      # ----------------------------\n      resp_score =\n        2 * hx_copd +\n        1.5 * hx_asthma,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # METABOLIC / ENDOCRINE\n      # ----------------------------\n      metabolic_score =\n        2 * hx_diabetes_type2 +\n        1.5 * hx_diabetes_type1 +\n        1.5 * hx_obesity +\n        1 * hx_hyperthyroidism +\n        1 * hx_hypothyroidism,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # ORGAN FAILURE\n      # ----------------------------\n      organ_score =\n        3 * hx_ckd +\n        2 * hx_liver_disease,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # IMMUNE / ONCOLOGY (VERY HIGH RISK)\n      # ----------------------------\n      immune_score =\n        3 * hx_immunosuppressed +\n        3 * hx_malignancy +\n        2 * hx_hiv +\n        2 * hx_coagulopathy,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # NEURO / OTHER\n      # ----------------------------\n      neuro_score =\n        1.5 * hx_epilepsy +\n        1 * hx_dementia,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # BEHAVIOURAL / SOCIAL (lower acute risk)\n      # ----------------------------\n      social_score =\n        1 * hx_substance_use_disorder +\n        0.5 * hx_depression +\n        0.5 * hx_anxiety,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # SPECIAL POPULATIONS\n      # ----------------------------\n      special_score =\n        2 * hx_pregnant,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # TOTAL RAW SCORE\n      # ----------------------------\n      risk_score_raw =\n        cardio_score +\n        resp_score +\n        metabolic_score +\n        organ_score +\n        immune_score +\n        neuro_score +\n        social_score +\n        special_score,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # INTERACTION BOOSTS (KEY IMPROVEMENT)\n      # ----------------------------\n      interaction_bonus =\n        2 * (hx_heart_failure & hx_ckd) +\n        2 * (hx_diabetes_type2 & hx_ckd) +\n        2 * (hx_malignancy & hx_immunosuppressed) +\n        1.5 * (hx_copd & hx_heart_failure) +\n        1.5 * (hx_obesity & hx_diabetes_type2),\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # FINAL ADJUSTED SCORE\n      # ----------------------------\n      risk_score_adj = risk_score_raw + interaction_bonus,\n      \n      # ----------------------------\n      # SCALE TO 1–10\n      # ----------------------------\n      risk_score = scales::rescale(risk_score_adj, to = c(1, 10))\n    )\n}\n\n\n# Prepare data\n\ndeterioration_model <- create_risk_score(patient_history)\n\nX <-deterioration_model %>%\n  select(starts_with(\"hx_\"))\n\ny <- deterioration_model$risk_score\n\n# matrix format\nX_matrix <- as.matrix(X)\n\n\n\n# Train model\n\nlibrary(lightgbm)\n\ndtrain <- lgb.Dataset(data = X_matrix, label = y)\n\nparams <- list(\n  objective = \"regression\",\n  metric = \"rmse\",\n  learning_rate = 0.05,\n  num_leaves = 31,\n  min_data_in_leaf = 20,\n  feature_fraction = 0.8,\n  bagging_fraction = 0.8,\n  bagging_freq = 1,\n  lambda_l2 = 2.0,\n  verbosity = -1\n)\n\nmodel <- lgb.train(\n  params = params,\n  data = dtrain,\n  nrounds = 200\n)\n\n\n# Prediction\n\npreds <- predict(model, X_matrix)\n\n# keep within 1–10\npreds <- pmin(pmax(preds, 1), 10)\n\n\nrisk_category <- function(x) {\n  case_when(\n    x >= 9 ~ \"EXTREME (Immediate resuscitation)\",\n    x >= 8 ~ \"CRITICAL (Immediate attention)\",\n    x >= 7 ~ \"VERY HIGH (Urgent, rapid review)\",\n    x >= 6 ~ \"HIGH (Urgent)\",\n    x >= 5 ~ \"MODERATE-HIGH (Early review)\",\n    x >= 4 ~ \"MODERATE (Monitor closely)\",\n    x >= 3 ~ \"LOW-MODERATE (Routine monitoring)\",\n    x >= 2 ~ \"LOW (Stable)\",\n    TRUE   ~ \"MINIMAL (Well / low concern)\"\n  )\n}\n\n\ndeterioration_model$predicted_risk <- preds\ndeterioration_model$deterioration_risk <- risk_category(preds)\n\nhead(deterioration_model)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## ✅ Summary\n\nThis notebook demonstrates a hybrid triage system combining:\n\n- ✅ Structured ML (LightGBM)\n- ✅ NLP interpretation of complaints\n- ✅ Comorbidity-driven deterioration scoring\n\nTogether, these components provide a **multi-dimensional view of patient risk**, supporting more informed triage decisions.\n\n---\n\n💡 Future improvements:\n- Add vitals & time-series data\n- Replace rule-based NLP with transformer models\n- Train deterioration risk using real outcomes\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"","metadata":{}}]}